---
import MainLayout from "../layout/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="About Abhilash Kumar Panda"
  seoTitle="About Abhilash Kumar Panda | Senior Data Scientist"
  seoDesc="9 years spanning financial markets operations and applied AI. The story of how pension fund reconciliation became the foundation for £600K+ in GenAI value.">

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16">

    <!-- ═══ ORIGIN STORY ═══ -->
    <div class="mb-20">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <div class="h-px w-10 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#4461f2] to-transparent"></div>
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[#4461f2]/50 uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">Origin Story</span>
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-8 leading-tight">
        <span class="text-white">Why financial AI</span><br/>
        <span class="bg-clip-text text-transparent bg-gradient-to-r from-[#4461f2] to-[#bc52ee]">built by someone who lived it</span><br/>
        <span class="text-white">works differently.</span>
      </h1>

      <div class="space-y-5 text-lg text-white/55 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        <p>
          In 2017, I joined State Street Global Advisory as a Reconciliation Analyst. Every day: Bloomberg Terminal,
          Refinitiv Eikon, SmartStream TLM. Reconciling 100+ managed pension fund portfolios — equities, derivatives,
          FX, post-trade settlement, corporate actions. The grinding, precise, high-stakes work of institutional asset management.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most people would see that as a detour before a "real" tech career. <span class="text-white/80">I see it as the most important
          thing I ever did.</span> Because when I crossed over to data science at LSEG in 2019, I didn't just bring Python and
          statistics — I brought an intimate understanding of the data I was now being asked to automate.
        </p>
        <p>
          I knew why Korean regulatory filings were structured the way they were. I knew what made a broker report
          ambiguous. I knew which edge cases would break a production system in the third month, not the third day.
          <span class="text-white/80">That knowledge is not in any dataset. You get it by living inside the domain.</span>
        </p>
        <p>
          Nine years in, £600K+ delivered, 55 FTEs automated across global financial workflows —
          I'm looking for the next stage: <span class="text-white/80">Singapore's fintech and financial services ecosystem.</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ MY UNFAIR ADVANTAGE ═══ -->
    <div class="mb-20 p-7 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-[#4461f2]/10 to-[#bc52ee]/8
                border border-[#4461f2]/20 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-64 h-64 bg-[#bc52ee]/10 rounded-full blur-3xl -translate-y-1/2 translate-x-1/2 pointer-events-none"></div>
      <div class="relative">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[#4461f2]/60 uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">The edge</span>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-2 mb-6">My unfair advantage</h2>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          {[
            {
              icon: "◈",
              title: "Domain-first",
              desc: "I understand the financial instruments, workflows, and failure modes of the systems I'm automating — before a single line of code."
            },
            {
              icon: "◇",
              title: "Commercially accurate",
              desc: "My AI systems are optimised for business outcomes, not benchmark scores. £600K+ in delivered value is the only benchmark that matters."
            },
            {
              icon: "△",
              title: "Full-stack AI",
              desc: "From data extraction pipelines to agentic orchestration to LLM fine-tuning to LLMOps. I ship systems end-to-end."
            }
          ].map(a => (
            <div>
              <span class="text-2xl text-[#4461f2]/60">{a.icon}</span>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mt-2 mb-1">{a.title}</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">{a.desc}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ THREE CHAPTERS ═══ -->
    <div class="mb-20">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-white/25 uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">Career arc</span>
        <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-white/5"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-12">Three chapters</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8 relative">
        <div class="absolute left-[1.1rem] top-6 bottom-6 w-px bg-gradient-to-b from-amber-400/40 via-blue-400/40 to-purple-400/40 hidden md:block"></div>

        <!-- Chapter 1 -->
        <div class="md:pl-16 relative">
          <div class="hidden md:flex absolute left-0 top-1 h-9 w-9 rounded-full border-2 border-amber-400/40 bg-amber-500/10
                      items-center justify-center text-amber-400 text-xs font-bold">
            I
          </div>
          <div class="mb-2 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Reconciliation Analyst</h3>
            <span class="px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 text-amber-400/80 text-xs">Domain Foundation</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-amber-400/60 text-sm mb-1">State Street Global Advisory · Bangalore · Feb 2017 – Oct 2019</p>
          <p class="text-white/40 text-sm mb-4 italic">Learning the language of financial markets.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2.5">
            {[
              "Reconciled 100+ managed pension fund portfolios — equities, derivatives, FX — using Bloomberg Terminal, Refinitiv Eikon, and SmartStream TLM",
              "Managed daily multi-currency position/cash reconciliation and corporate actions (M&A, dividends, tender offers)",
              "Built PowerBI exception-trend dashboard for Portfolio Managers — the first AI-adjacent work, directly driven by frontline data pain",
              "Deep institutional asset management expertise: cross-custodian workflows, post-trade settlement, regulatory reporting — this became the domain foundation for everything at LSEG"
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5 text-sm text-white/55">
                <svg class="flex-shrink-0 h-4 w-4 text-amber-400/60 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                </svg>
                <span>{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Chapter 2 -->
        <div class="md:pl-16 relative">
          <div class="hidden md:flex absolute left-0 top-1 h-9 w-9 rounded-full border-2 border-blue-400/40 bg-blue-500/10
                      items-center justify-center text-blue-400 text-xs font-bold">
            II
          </div>
          <div class="mb-2 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Data Scientist</h3>
            <span class="px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-blue-500/10 border border-blue-500/20 text-blue-400/80 text-xs">Applied ML</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-blue-400/60 text-sm mb-1">London Stock Exchange Group · Bangalore · Nov 2019 – Oct 2022</p>
          <p class="text-white/40 text-sm mb-4 italic">Turning domain knowledge into production ML pipelines.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2.5">
            {[
              "Korean regulatory filing extraction: 85%+ hit rate, £250K+ savings, 5 FTE reduction — processing cut from 15 days to 40 minutes across 130K+ documents",
              "Hybrid ML + rule-based ingestion (cosine similarity, two-stage classification) across CA, IN, US, AU — saved 3 FTEs, cut out-of-scope data by 50%",
              "Two-stage document intelligence pipeline (Azure Layout Model + Python rules) — expanded image-based document coverage from 0% to 64%, eliminating 5 FTEs"
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5 text-sm text-white/55">
                <svg class="flex-shrink-0 h-4 w-4 text-blue-400/60 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                </svg>
                <span>{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Chapter 3 -->
        <div class="md:pl-16 relative">
          <div class="hidden md:flex absolute left-0 top-1 h-9 w-9 rounded-full border-2 border-purple-400/40 bg-purple-500/10
                      items-center justify-center text-purple-400 text-xs font-bold">
            III
          </div>
          <div class="mb-2 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Senior Data Scientist</h3>
            <span class="px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-purple-500/10 border border-purple-500/20 text-purple-400/80 text-xs">GenAI Leadership</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-purple-400/60 text-sm mb-1">London Stock Exchange Group · Bangalore · Nov 2022 – Present</p>
          <p class="text-white/40 text-sm mb-4 italic">Leading the shift from ML to GenAI — with financial domain embedded from the start.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2.5">
            {[
              "Built GenAI financial data extraction pipeline (meta-prompting, PydanticAI) — £350K+ savings and 50 FTE reduction",
              "Developed context-aware RAG Answer Engine — source-referenced responses, session memory, optimised prompt design for analyst productivity",
              "Led multi-agent AI PoC for financial document intelligence — earned regional executive endorsement",
              "Mentored data scientists; translated financial domain knowledge into scalable AI pipelines"
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5 text-sm text-white/55">
                <svg class="flex-shrink-0 h-4 w-4 text-purple-400/60 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                </svg>
                <span>{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ TECHNICAL SKILLS ═══ -->
    <div class="mb-20">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-white/25 uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">Toolkit</span>
        <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-white/5"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-8">Technical skills</h2>

      <div class="space-y-3">
        {[
          { label: "GenAI & Agents", skills: ["LangChain", "LangGraph", "Pydantic-AI", "MCP", "RAG", "Vector DB", "Agentic AI", "Prompt Engineering", "Context Engineering"] },
          { label: "LLMs", skills: ["OpenAI GPT-4", "Gemini", "Claude", "LLaMA (fine-tuned)", "HuggingFace", "Unsloth", "vLLM", "LiteLLM"] },
          { label: "ML / Deep Learning", skills: ["PyTorch", "TensorFlow", "Scikit-learn", "NLP", "Computer Vision", "Statistical Modeling", "BERT", "Transformers"] },
          { label: "Cloud & LLMOps", skills: ["GCP", "Azure", "Azure Document Intelligence", "LLMOps", "CI/CD", "CML Pipelines", "MLflow", "ZenML", "DVC", "Docker"] },
          { label: "Languages & APIs", skills: ["Python", "SQL", "FastAPI", "Flask"] }
        ].map(cat => (
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-x-4 gap-y-2 py-3 border-b border-white/5">
            <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-white/30 uppercase tracking-wider w-36 flex-shrink-0">{cat.label}</span>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
              {cat.skills.map(s => (
                <span class="skill-pill">{s}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ EDUCATION & CERTS ═══ -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-20">

      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <span class="text-xs font-mono text-white/25 uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">Education</span>
          <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-white/5"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          {[
            { degree: "PG Diploma, Finance & Operations", school: "ISME, Bangalore", period: "2015 – 2017" },
            { degree: "B.Tech, Mechanical Engineering", school: "Silicon Institute of Technology, Odisha", period: "2010 – 2014" }
          ].map(edu => (
            <div class="p-5 rounded-xl bg-white/5 border border-white/10 hover:border-white/20 transition-all">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/90">{edu.degree}</h3>
              <p class="text-white/45 text-sm mt-1">{edu.school}</p>
              <p class="text-white/25 text-xs mt-1 font-mono">{edu.period}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <span class="text-xs font-mono text-white/25 uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">Certifications</span>
          <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-white/5"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          {[
            { title: "PG Programme in Data Science", org: "INSOFE / Carnegie Mellon University", icon: "🎓" },
            { title: "Machine Learning in Production", org: "Andrew Ng · Coursera", icon: "📚" },
            { title: "Complete MCP Developer Guide", org: "Udemy", icon: "🔧" },
            { title: "Six Sigma Green Belt", org: "KPMG", icon: "📊" }
          ].map(cert => (
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3.5 rounded-xl bg-white/5 border border-white/10 hover:border-white/20 transition-all">
              <span class="text-lg">{cert.icon}</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/85">{cert.title}</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-white/35 mt-0.5">{cert.org}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ NEXT CHAPTER ═══ -->
    <div class="p-7 rounded-2xl border border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-500/5">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-emerald-400 mt-2 flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse"></span>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Open to opportunities</h2>
          <p class="text-white/55 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Seeking senior IC and lead roles in Singapore's fintech and financial services ecosystem.
            If you're building production AI in financial markets and want someone who actually understands both sides, let's talk.
          </p>
          <a href="mailto:abhilash.k.panda@gmail.com"
             class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-r from-[#4461f2] to-[#bc52ee]
                    text-white text-sm font-medium hover:opacity-90 transition-all">
            abhilash.k.panda@gmail.com →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .skill-pill {
    @apply px-2.5 py-1 text-xs rounded-lg bg-white/5 text-white/50 border border-white/10
           hover:text-white/70 hover:border-white/20 transition-colors cursor-default;
  }
</style>
